a，Therefore, sharing what you're good at and locking it down — for the world and for yourself — is deeply meaningful

588
00:58:34.653 --> 00:58:37.528
b，The opportunity cost is zero.

589
00:58:37.528 --> 00:58:42.740
Time is linear, but memory is hyperbolic — the precious kind is doubly so.

590
00:58:42.740 --> 00:58:48.678
Also: your destination / future is you, and your past / experiences are also you.

591
00:58:48.678 --> 00:58:54.778
That part of yourself is equally important — not only the future-goal-achieving self that matters most.

592
00:58:54.778 --> 00:59:04.378
c，Beyond your "near-term goals," there is always something — unrelated to those goals, but best done now rather than later — like traveling the world, or staying up all night playing cards

593
00:59:04.378 --> 00:59:09.065
5.10.3 Small-scale sharing, or large-scale sharing?

594
00:59:09.065 --> 00:59:11.928
My personal preference is the latter.

595
00:59:11.928 --> 00:59:18.278
5.10.3.1 Mr. J said his strongest math competition skill is Algorithms.

596
00:59:18.278 --> 00:59:20.428
He shared it at scale.

597
00:59:20.428 --> 00:59:27.965
Now everyone knows "The Supreme Method" — it rescues your mindset collapse during exams and snaps you out of being stuck on a weird problem.

598
00:59:27.965 --> 00:59:32.178
Faithful transmission, great benefit to those who come after.

599
00:59:32.178 --> 00:59:37.453
5.10.3.2 You don't know the large-scale readers who find your work.

600
00:59:37.453 --> 00:59:49.328
In terms of meaning, influence, and durability — is it better to have "100 former national team members think you're the best," or "5,000 devoted fans and maybe hundreds of thousands of later generations think so"?

601
00:59:49.328 --> 00:59:51.590
Actually, the latter.

602
00:59:51.590 --> 00:59:58.215
a，First, there's a world of difference in rarity between having great medical skill and advancing medical science.

603
00:59:58.215 --> 01:00:03.865
Every dynasty had great doctors — but how many truly important medical texts have there been?

604
01:00:03.865 --> 01:00:07.578
In Chinese medicine, the answer is fewer than ten.

605
01:00:07.578 --> 01:00:15.840
b，Second, most people will be completely forgotten within 150 years — three generations, once everyone who remembers you is gone.

606
01:00:15.840 --> 01:00:24.678
A technique that people use every day, woven into the basic fabric of a community — that is the only way to defeat time and achieve immortality.*

607
01:00:24.678 --> 01:00:32.278
5.10.4 In making money and building things, the author is only at the provincial / junior olympiad level.

608
01:00:32.278 --> 01:00:43.890
But books that address "how ordinary people go from their first pot of gold to permanent financial freedom" and "how extraordinary people serve original dishes to the world" — at a geometric level — are almost nonexistent.

609
01:00:43.890 --> 01:00:48.503
Writing this for first-year math competition students is what I should be doing.

610
01:00:48.503 --> 01:00:52.928
5.10.5 There is one gold standard for this.

611
01:00:52.928 --> 01:00:57.953
When I was a freshman, would I have wanted to live in a world where 5hows existed?

612
01:00:57.953 --> 01:01:01.590
Twenty years back from the start, my answer is yes.

613
01:01:01.590 --> 01:01:05.503
Now that it's written, I've kept faith with my younger self.

614
01:01:05.503 --> 01:01:07.128
That's all.

615
01:01:07.128 --> 01:01:09.990
RynW1988

